    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-09-19T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-09-19T17:00:00-05:00" n="886"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d886">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">817.1051/685: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_HME1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hanna</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-09-19T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 19, 1932—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>95. Your 176, September 16, 3 p.m. Department has no objection to President
                        <persName corresp="#p_MJM2">Moncada</persName>’s suggestion that the
                    candidates should sign an agreement in your presence that they will carry out
                    the provisions <pb facs="0978" n="874" xml:id="pg_874"/> of the plan proposed by
                    the Commander of the Guardia and accepted by President <persName
                        corresp="#p_MJM2">Moncada</persName>, for the appointment of the higher
                    officers in the Guardia.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SHL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
